			
			â­ï¸ â­ï¸ â­ï¸ â­ï¸ â­ï¸ HOW TO GET THE POSITION AND DIMENSION OF AN ELEMENT : â­ï¸ â­ï¸ â­ï¸ â­ï¸ â­ï¸ 

ğŸŸ¡ï¸ use : getBoundingClientRect()

ğŸ‘ï¸â€ğŸ—¨ï¸ï¸ ğŸ‘ï¸â€ğŸ—¨ï¸ï¸ ğŸ‘ï¸â€ğŸ—¨ï¸ï¸ The getBoundingClientRect() method is not available directly on the EventTarget type. 
To access it, you need to ensure that the target element is an HTMLElement.
Hence, checkout ğŸ—¯ï¸

ğŸ‘‰ï¸ example.tsx:

import React, { useState } from "react";

const MyComponent = () => {
  const [position, setPosition] = useState({ x: 0, y: 0 });

  const handleClick = (e) => {
    const target = e.target as HTMLElement; ğŸ—¯ï¸
    const rect = target.getBoundingClientRect();
    setPosition({ x: rect.left, y: rect.top });
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
      <p>Position: {`(${position.x}, ${position.y})`}</p>
    </div>
  );
};

export default MyComponent;

PROPERTIES:
DOMRect {
	bottom: number
	height : number
	left : number
	right : number
	top : number
	width : number
	x : number
	y : number
}
